Multiple entries within a single cell (e.g., co-leads, other collaborators, SDGs) are separated by semicolons (";").\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls12\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	
\f2 \uc0\u8259 
\f1 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Country names follow the World Bank country list (https://data.worldbank.org/country).\
\ls12\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	
\f2 \uc0\u8259 
\f1 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Chinese government body names omit the suffix "of the People's Republic of China" for brevity.\
\ls12\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	
\f2 \uc0\u8259 
\f1 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Environmental problems are coded using an 11-category typology adapted from the IISD framework (see codebook for full definitions).\
\ls12\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	
\f2 \uc0\u8259 
\f1 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Actor types are coded into six categories: national government; subnational government; business; civil society; university/research institute; others. International collaborators may also be coded as "international organization".\
